  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Large crustaceans with distinctive facial mandibles.=
</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Wekkarus</span> live deep in th=
e seas
  of Ocean planets. They can also live out of water for extended periods, b=
ut
  prefer a damp environment.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>They construct entire underwater cities in the vast
  caverns and tunnels of the ocean worlds they inhabit. These cities are
  centers of technology and industry, manufacturing advanced underwater
  technology that is used throughout the galaxy.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The deep undersea tunnels that the <span class=3DSpe=
llE>Wekkarus</span>
  inhabit are also the home to an abundance of other marine life &#8211; so=
me
  of it hostile. <span class=3DSpellE>Wekkarus</span> fear one predator in
  particular: the leviathan <span class=3DSpellE>Darkhul</span>, a formidab=
le
  deep-sea monster that grows to lengths of 100 meters or more.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Wekkarus</span> have adapted to=
 these
  threats by developing powerful force-fields that guard the entrances to t=
heir
  underwater colonies.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Wekkarus</span> also have d=
eep
  knowledge of highly specialized Wave Beam weapons. This has led them to
  develop the potent <span class=3DSpellE>PulseWave</span> weapon. This uni=
que
  type of beam weapon fires powerful waves of energy at targets.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Wekkarus</span> are a generally
  peaceful species that like to keep to themselves.</p>
